And you might consider trying <a href="http://www.emucr.com/search/label/NES" class="postlink">FCEUX SVN</a> (development) versions instead, as fixes/etc. tend to get added to those much sooner.  I should note, however, that one of the recent SVNs crashed when reading fceux.cfg from an older version of FCEUX SVN, so I recommend writing down what all the tweaks/changes you apply to the emulator (preferences, input, etc.) before switching.<br /><br />Same advice applies for Nestopia as well (site has Nestopia unofficial builds on there, though there hasn't been one in a while).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Sat Feb 07, 2015 4:48 pm</p><hr />
